name: Prediction Probability Chart
text: The index of data points is represented on the X-axis, and the predicted probability is presented on the Y-axis.

name: Precision-Recall Curve
text: A precision-recall curve ( or PR Curve) is a plot of the precision (y-axis) and the recall (x-axis) for different probability thresholds.

name: Multiclass Precision-Recall Curve
text: Precision-Recall Curve for each class separately.

name: ROC Curve
text: A ROC curve (receiver operating characteristic curve) is a graph showing the performance of a classification model at all classification thresholds.

name: Multiclass ROC Curve
text: ROC curve for each class separately.

name: TPR FPR at every threshold
text: X-axis represents threshold, Y-axis represents TPR and FPR

name: Gain Chart
text: Gain is the ratio between the cumulative number of positive(favorable) data points up to a percentage to the total number of positive data points in the data.

name: Lift Chart
text: Lift is a statistic that compares a given model's performance to that of a random model.
